Setup a new WGT Project using the WGT Wizard

--------------------------------------------
1. Got to "File, New, Other" in your Eclipse workspace and 
select the "WGT Project wizard" from the list.
--------------------------------------------

[../images/screens/plugin/wizard01.jpg] Wizard 1

--------------------------------------------
2. Enter the the required Parameters for your Project (Minimum Project name and Package). 
Click "Finish"
--------------------------------------------

[../images/screens/plugin/wizard02.jpg] Wizard 2

--------------------------------------------
3. When the project was created, select it an go to 
"MyEclipse, Project Capabilities, Add Web Project Capabilities";
--------------------------------------------

[../images/screens/plugin/capabilities01.jpg] Wizard 3

--------------------------------------------
4. Enter your "Web context root", select your Java Version and click "Finish".
--------------------------------------------

[../images/screens/plugin/capabilities02.jpg] Wizard 4

--------------------------------------------
5. Deploy the new Project to your local MyEclipse Tomcat and start the server
--------------------------------------------

[../images/screens/plugin/deploy.jpg] Wizard 5

--------------------------------------------
6. Go to your favourite browser and enter the new URL of your application. 
In most cases it will be http://localhost:8080/<your web context root from step 4> 
--------------------------------------------

[../images/screens/plugin/hello_wgt.jpg] Wizard 6

--------------------------------------------
6. A welcome Page-class was created for you. This class is ready for your development
--------------------------------------------